          <Comment>This sequence change creates a premature translational stop signal (p.Leu480Argfs*11) in the COL6A2 gene. It is expected to result in an absent or disrupted protein product. Loss-of-function variants in COL6A2 are known to be pathogenic (PMID: 19884007, 20976770). This variant is not present in population databases (gnomAD no frequency). This variant has not been reported in the literature in individuals affected with COL6A2-related conditions. For these reasons, this variant has been classified as Pathogenic.</Comment>
